cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.IR, cs.NE 

This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of cs.CL (Computation and Language) as it deals with natural language processing (NLP) and information extraction from biomedical literature. The use of deep learning models and attention mechanisms also suggests a possible fit with the sub-categories of cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Additionally, the distant supervision approach used to construct a larger dataset may align with the sub-categories of cs.IR (Information Retrieval) and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
